ORIGINAL WORK STATEMENT:
All item language in the SCDCI is original. No text has been
reproduced from copyrighted source measures. The SCDCI's conceptual
structure is informed by published theoretical frameworks, which are
cited for academic transparency — not reproduced. Specifically:

  - The Learning Style Profile© Checklist (LSP-C) is copyright
    Rydell, Lyons, & Harris (2025). The SCDCI does not reproduce
    LSP-C items, rating scales, or scoring procedures.

  - The Functional Emotional Developmental Capacities (FEDC) Basic
    Chart is published by the Interdisciplinary Council on
    Development and Learning (ICDL). The SCDCI does not reproduce
    FEDC items or rating procedures.

  - The Behavioral, Emotional, and Social Skills Inventory (BESSI)
    is copyright Soto, Napolitano, Sewell, Yoon, & Roberts (2022).
    The SCDCI does not reproduce BESSI items or scoring algorithms.

  - The Social Skills Framework (SSF) is from Ross, Toth, Heggestad,
    & Banks (2025). Conceptual type classifications are used for
    construct validity — no SSF content is reproduced.

  - The Treatment Resource Manual, 6th Edition, is copyright
    Roth & Worthington (2021), published by Plural Publishing.
    Treatment bridges reference published clinical principles —
    no text is reproduced.

  - Multimodal SST research is from Nakamura (2025). No content
    is reproduced.

These citations are provided for academic integrity and to establish
the theoretical basis of the SCDCI. They do not imply endorsement
by, affiliation with, or licensing from the cited authors or
publishers.

